Parliament, Monday, 13 August 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Labour will this week conduct oversight visits in Gauteng and Free State provinces to look into conditions of employment in several industries. Tomorrow (Tuesday), the committee will visit the North Rand Training Centre at the Randjesfontein Race Course in Gauteng for a meeting with the Horse Grooms Association and to inspect the stables and the grooms’hostels. On Wednesday, the committee will conduct oversight at the Beatrix Mine in Welkom, Free State, where 955 mineworkers were trapped underground for more than a day, earlier this year, following a power failure.The committee will also meet with workers and management in the retail and wholesale sector in Motheo District Municipality. Click here to view the full programme for the oversight visit. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON LABOUR, MR LEMIAS MASHILE For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson,please contact: Name: Sakhile Mokoena
